nd immigration laws, displacement, exile, and the pain and losses he endured hidden behind a popular public image.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAsian diaspora. 0aChinese American artistsvBiography. 0aChinese American authorsvBiography. 0aChinese in literature. 0aChinesezEnglandvBiography. 0aChinesezUnited StatesvBiography. 0aExiles' writings, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 0aTravelers' writings, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aDanto, Arthur C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081354927940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813549279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813549279/original  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK